Delek Energy Surges on Report Delek Group Planning Offer

-- B y   S u s a n   L e r n e r
-- 
2011-06-22T12:52:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-22/delek-energy-surges-on-report-delek-group-planning-offer-1-.html
Delek Energy Systems Ltd. (DLEN)  headed for
the biggest gain since November 2009 after Globes reported  Delek
Group Ltd. (DLEKG)  plans to take the company private in a transaction
that may value the shares at 1,500 shekels each.  Delek Energy shares soared 10 percent to 1,270 shekels at
3:21 p.m. in  Tel Aviv .  Delek Group may offer shares of Delek Drilling-LP and
Avner Oil Exploration-LP in exchange for the publicly held
shares of Delek Energy,  Globes reported , without saying where it
got the information.  A spokesman for Delek Group, who couldn’t be identified
because of company policy, declined to comment when contacted by
Bloomberg News. Delek Group owns 79.9 percent of Delek Energy
Systems, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  Delek Energy owns stakes in the Tamar and Leviathan gas
fields off  Israel ’s coast, through its 50 percent holding in
Delek Drilling and 47 percent stake in Avner. The two sites
together may hold 25 trillion cubic feet of natural gas, double
the U.K.’s proven reserves in 2009, Noble Energy Inc., the
Houston-based operator of the sites, has said.  The shares of Delek Group increased 3 percent to 748.1
shekels, while Delek Drilling shares dropped 2.2 percent to
11.14 shekels and Avner shares declined 1.6 percent to 2.047
shekels.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Susan Lerner in Jerusalem at 
